gomodel:SYNGO_2246  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099056 replaced by GO:0042734" , "Rationale: - PTPRS immunoreactivity was present in a punctate pattern decorating the dendrites of cultured hippocampal neurons at DIV 15 and these puncta overlapped with VGLUT1, but not with VGAT.\n- Furthermore, PTPRS puncta were apposed to PSD-95 puncta in brain in hippocampal CA1 region.\n\n15/01/2018 Pim\n- Literal: \"PTPσ immunoreactivity was also present in a punctate pattern decorating the dendrites of cultured hippocampal neurons at DIV 15, and these puncta overlapped with VGLUT1 (Figure 3E). PTPσ puncta overlapping VGLUT1 were also observed on axons not contacting dendrites, suggesting an axonal localization (Figure 3E, arrowheads).'\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: Experimental Procedures\nCell Cultures, Transfection, and Immunocytochemistry\nCultures of hippocampal neurons, neuron-fibroblast cocultures, and immunocytochemistry were performed essentially as described (Linhoff et al., 2009).\n\nM.W. Linhoff, J. Lauren, R.M. Cassidy, F.A. Dobie, H. Takahashi, H.B. Nygaard, M.S. Airaksinen, S.M. Strittmatter, A.M. Craig\nAn unbiased expression screen for synaptogenic proteins identifies the LRRTM protein family as synaptic organizers. Neuron, 61 (2009)\nExperimental Procedures\nCell Culture\nCultures of hippocampal neurons were prepared from E18 rat embryos." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5518-6584" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6194-9648" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
